miscConds.notes: AS TO BOTH COUNTS: Pay all court costs, fees, and surcharges including DNA; all applicable fees of supervision by the end of supervision. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation department.
- Absolute/maintain sobriety, no alcohol, no drugs.
- No possession/consumption/selling/distribution of illegal drugs/alcohol.
- Random urine screens.
- Obtain/maintain full time employment/education/vocation unless a physician indicates he is unable to do so.
- Provide a DNA sample.
- Follow all rules of supervision and follow through with any other treatment deemed necessary by the department.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Kamelle Maurice Williamson in court with attorney Scott Franklin Anderson.  Zachary A Wittchow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

As to Count 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve  1 YEAR at the House of Corrections with 2 days credit CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence but CONCURRENT to Count 2.  First 6 months straight time, remainder with Huber release.

As to Count 2:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve  1 YEAR at the House of Corrections with 2 days credit CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence but CONCURRENT to Count 1.  First 6 months straight time, remainder with Huber release.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on 2 YEARS probation.

  Conditions of Probation:
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation department.
- Absolute/maintain sobriety, no alcohol, no drugs.
- No possession/consumption/selling/distribution of illegal drugs/alcohol.
- Random urine screens.
- Obtain/maintain fulltime employment/education/vocation unless a physician indicates he is unable to do so.
- Provide a DNA sample.
- Follow all rules of supervision and follow through with any other treatment deemed necessary by the department.

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
All court costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA); 
All applicable fees of supervision.
-  Cash bail on deposit to be applied if applicable. 

Filed:   
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement
